        "result": "task_id: ses_361eeeb3affess5WZor82uB97b (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive analysis of every TypeScript file in `src/`:\n\n---\n\n## `src/types.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/types.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Central type definitions file — the single source of truth for all shared interfaces and types used throughout the codebase.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `interface BeadInfo` — Represents a task/ticket (bead) with id, title, description, status, labels, priority, dependsOn, blocks, type, parentId\n- `interface LoopConfig` — Full configuration shape from `.super-ralph/config.toml` (engine settings, opencode URL, CLI path, models, reverse/decompose options)\n- `interface IterationResult` — Result of a single agent loop iteration including status, cost, tokens, filesChanged, transcriptPath\n- `interface CompletionResult` — The signal an agent sends when finishing a task (status + optional reason)\n- `interface LoopResult` — Aggregate result of an entire phase loop (completed/failed/skipped counts, totalTime, iterations array)\n- `interface PhaseFlags` — Base flags shared by all three phases (dryRun, maxIterations, modelOverride, attach)\n- `interface ForwardFlags extends PhaseFlags` — Adds `epicId`\n- `interface DecomposeFlags extends PhaseFlags` — Adds `specPath`, `epicTitle`\n- `interface ReverseFlags extends PhaseFlags` — Adds `inputs`, `outputDir`, `skill`, `interactive`, `answersFile`\n- `type ErrorStrategy` — `\"retry\" | \"skip\" | \"abort\"`\n\n**Dependencies:** None (pure type declarations).\n\n---\n\n## `src/beads.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/beads.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Thin adapter layer around the `br` CLI tool — spawns `br` as a subprocess, parses its JSON output, and translates the results into typed `BeadInfo` objects for the rest of the framework.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `async function runBr(args, cwd?)` — Generic `br` command runner; returns parsed JSON\n- `async function getAllReady(epicId)` — Returns all unblocked beads in an epic (sorted by hybrid priority)\n- `async function getBeadDetails(beadId)` — Returns full details for one bead\n- `async function closeBead(beadId, reason?)` — Closes a bead and returns newly unblocked beads\n- `async function getAllBeads(epicId)` — Returns all child beads of an epic\n- `async function getEpicProgress(epicId)` — Returns `{ total, completed, remaining }` counts\n\n**Dependencies:** `./types.js` (`BeadInfo`)\n\n---\n\n## `src/config.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/config.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Loads and merges `.super-ralph/config.toml` with hardcoded defaults, and provides a model-resolution function that picks the right AI model based on bead labels, area mappings, or CLI overrides.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `function loadConfig(projectDir)` — Reads and deep-merges TOML config with defaults; returns a `LoopConfig`\n- `function resolveModel(beadLabels, beadTitle, config, cliOverride?)` — Returns `{ providerID, modelID }` by priority: CLI override → bead area label → config default\n\n**Dependencies:** `./types.js` (`LoopConfig`, `ErrorStrategy`); external: `@iarna/toml`, `fs`, `path`\n\n---\n\n## `src/template.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/template.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Minimal wrapper around Handlebars for loading and rendering `.hbs` prompt templates stored in `.super-ralph/`.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `function loadTemplate(projectDir, filename?)` — Reads a `.hbs` file from `.super-ralph/` and compiles it via Handlebars; throws if missing\n- `function renderPrompt(template, vars)` — Executes a compiled Handlebars template with the given variables\n\n**Dependencies:** External: `handlebars`, `fs`, `path`. No internal src/ dependencies.\n\n---\n\n## `src/output-parser.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/output-parser.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Provides a `StreamCapture` class that accumulates raw SSE event lines and human-readable display text during a session, capping total size at 250,000 characters to prevent memory bloat.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `class StreamCapture`\n  - `addRawLine(line)` — Appends a raw JSONL event line\n  - `addDisplayText(text)` — Appends display text (streamed model output)\n  - `toolStatusText(toolName, status, error?)` — Returns a human-readable status string for a tool call\n  - `getRawOutput()` — Returns the full raw event stream string\n  - `getDisplayOutput()` — Returns the full human-readable display string\n\n**Dependencies:** None (pure utility).\n\n---\n\n## `src/timeout.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/timeout.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Single-function utility that races a promise against a setTimeout to enforce a hard deadline, rejecting with a custom error message if exceeded.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `async function withTimeout<T>(task, timeoutMs, errorMessage)` — Returns the task result or throws if `timeoutMs` elapses first\n\n**Dependencies:** None.\n\n---\n\n## `src/events.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/events.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Defines the event system for the engine loop — a strongly-typed union of all possible engine lifecycle events, a lightweight pub/sub emitter, and a default console renderer that formats those events for terminal output.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `type EngineEvent` — Discriminated union of all event types (loop.description, server.started, iteration.started, iteration.completed, iteration.blocked, iteration.retrying, iteration.failed, iteration.error, loop.completed, etc.)\n- `type EngineEventListener` — `(event: EngineEvent) => void`\n- `class EngineEventEmitter` — Simple pub/sub emitter with `on(listener)` (returns detach fn) and `emit(event)`\n- `function attachDefaultConsoleRenderer(emitter)` — Registers a listener that logs all events to stdout/stderr with emoji formatting; returns detach function\n\n**Dependencies:** `./types.js` (`CompletionResult`)\n\n---\n\n## `src/run-state.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/run-state.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Manages per-run artifact persistence: creates a timestamped run directory under `.super-ralph/runs/`, writes a live `session.json` state file after every event, records events to a JSONL log, and writes per-iteration transcript files.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `interface RunTracker` — `{ runId, runDir, recordEvent(event), writeIterationTranscript(iteration, label, rawOutput?, displayOutput?), finalize(status) }`\n- `function startRunTracker(projectDir, description, maxIterations)` — Initializes the run directory + state files and returns a `RunTracker`\n\n**Dependencies:** `./events.js` (`EngineEvent`); external: `fs`, `path`\n\n---\n\n## `src/run-status.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/run-status.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Read-only companion to `run-state.ts` — resolves a run reference (exact ID or `\"latest\"`) and reads back the persisted session state, event count, last event info, and latest transcript path for the `status` command.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `interface RunSessionStatus` — Shape of `session.json` (runId, status, description, counters, timestamps)\n- `interface RunStatus` — Enriched status including eventCount, lastEventType, lastEventTimestamp, latestTranscript\n- `function getRunStatus(projectDir, runRef)` — Resolves `runRef` to a run directory and returns a populated `RunStatus`\n\n**Dependencies:** External: `fs`, `path`. No internal src/ dependencies.\n\n---\n\n## `src/progress.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/progress.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Appends human-readable Markdown progress entries to `.super-ralph/progress.md` after each iteration, and reads back the N most recent entries to give the agent context about what just happened.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `function readRecentProgress(projectDir, count?)` — Returns the last `count` iteration blocks from `progress.md` as a string\n- `function appendProgress(projectDir, iteration, result)` — Appends a formatted Markdown entry for one iteration result\n- `function formatProgressEntry(iteration, result)` — Formats a single `IterationResult` into a Markdown block (exported for testing)\n\n**Dependencies:** `./types.js` (`IterationResult`); external: `fs`, `path`\n\n---\n\n## `src/skills.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/skills.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Resolves a skill name or file path to its Markdown content, supporting both built-in skills (`feature`, `bug`, `hotfix`, `refactor`) and arbitrary user-supplied file paths.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `function loadSkill(skillNameOrPath, cliDir)` — Returns the content of the skill file, or `null` if no skill was specified\n- `function getCliDir()` — Returns the absolute path to the super-ralph CLI install directory (parent of `src/`) using `import.meta.url`\n\n**Dependencies:** External: `fs`, `path`. No internal src/ dependencies.\n\n---\n\n## `src/opencode.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/opencode.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Core OpenCode integration layer — manages server lifecycle (start/attach), session creation, real-time prompt streaming via SSE, and result extraction (task_complete detection, cost/token accounting, files changed).\n\n**Exports:**\n- `type OpencodeClient` — Re-exported from `@opencode-ai/sdk`\n- `interface PromptResult` — `{ completion, cost, tokens, filesChanged, rawOutput, displayOutput }`\n- `interface ServerHandle` — `{ client, url, close() }`\n- `function checkBrokenSymlinks(opts?)` — Scans `~/.config/opencode/` for broken plugin/command symlinks; optionally removes them; returns list of broken paths\n- `async function startServer()` — Spawns an ephemeral OpenCode server, verifies it's ready, returns a `ServerHandle`\n- `async function connectToServer(url)` — Connects to an existing OpenCode server, returns a `ServerHandle`\n- `async function createSession(client, title)` — Creates a new OpenCode session, returns its ID\n- `async function runPrompt(client, sessionId, prompt, model, systemPrompt?, serverUrl?, inactivityTimeoutMs?)` — Sends a prompt, streams SSE events to stdout in real-time (with inactivity watchdog + heartbeat), extracts and returns a `PromptResult`\n- `async function showToast(client, message, variant)` — Shows a toast in the OpenCode TUI\n- `async function abortSession(client, sessionId)` — Aborts a running session\n\n**Dependencies:** `./types.js` (`CompletionResult`), `./output-parser.js` (`StreamCapture`); external: `@opencode-ai/sdk`, `@opencode-ai/sdk/v2`, `fs`, `path`, `os`\n\n---\n\n## `src/interactive.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/interactive.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Handles the interactive reverse phase — subscribes to SSE events, intercepts `question.asked` events and renders them to the terminal via `@clack/prompts` (or auto-answers them from a pre-recorded mock answers file for testing), then collects the session result.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `type InteractiveClient` — Re-export of `OpencodeClient` from `@opencode-ai/sdk/v2`\n- `interface InteractiveResult` — `{ completion, cost, tokens, filesChanged, rawOutput, displayOutput }`\n- `interface MockAnswer` — `{ match: string; answer: string | number }` — for pre-recorded test answers\n- `function loadMockAnswers(filePath)` — Loads mock answers from a JSON file into module-level state\n- `function clearMockAnswers()` — Resets mock answer state\n- `function hasMockAnswersLoaded()` — Returns whether mock answers are active\n- `function getMockAnswerLog()` — Returns the log of questions asked and answers given during a mock session\n- `function createInteractiveClient(baseUrl)` — Creates a v2 OpenCode client needed for the question API\n- `async function runInteractiveSession(client, sessionId, prompt, model, systemPrompt?, inactivityTimeoutMs?)` — Runs an interactive SSE session, handling questions via clack or mock answers, and returns an `InteractiveResult`\n\n**Dependencies:** `./types.js` (`CompletionResult`), `./output-parser.js` (`StreamCapture`); external: `@opencode-ai/sdk/v2`, `@clack/prompts`, `fs`\n\n---\n\n## `src/engine.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/engine.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** The central orchestration engine — implements the generic `runPhaseLoop` function that drives all three phases (forward, decompose, reverse autonomous), managing iteration lifecycle, retry/skip/abort error strategies, event emission, run tracking, and timeout enforcement.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `interface PhaseIteration` — What `nextIteration` must return: `{ prompt, model, sessionTitle, iterationLabel, beadId?, systemPrompt? }`\n- `interface PhaseCallbacks` — The three hooks a phase must implement: `setup()`, `nextIteration()`, `handleResult()`\n- `async function runPhaseLoop(projectDir, callbacks, flags, onEvent?)` — The main loop; calls setup, then iterates calling nextIteration + runPrompt + handleResult until done or maxIterations reached; returns `LoopResult`\n\n**Dependencies:** `./config.js` (`loadConfig`), `./opencode.js` (`startServer`, `connectToServer`, `createSession`, `runPrompt`, `ServerHandle`), `./progress.js` (`appendProgress`), `./types.js` (`LoopConfig`, `LoopResult`, `IterationResult`, `CompletionResult`, `PhaseFlags`), `./events.js` (`EngineEventEmitter`, `attachDefaultConsoleRenderer`, `EngineEventListener`), `./run-state.js` (`startRunTracker`), `./timeout.js` (`withTimeout`)\n\n---\n\n## `src/forward.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/forward.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Implements the **Forward** phase — picks the highest-priority ready bead from an epic, renders a prompt for it, and drives the `runPhaseLoop` engine to implement and close beads one by one until all are done.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `async function runForward(projectDir, flags)` — Entrypoint for the forward phase; returns a `LoopResult`\n\n**Dependencies:** `./engine.js` (`runPhaseLoop`, `PhaseCallbacks`), `./beads.js` (`getAllBeads`, `getAllReady`, `getBeadDetails`, `getEpicProgress`), `./template.js` (`loadTemplate`, `renderPrompt`), `./progress.js` (`readRecentProgress`), `./config.js` (`resolveModel`), `./types.js` (`ForwardFlags`, `LoopResult`)\n\n---\n\n## `src/decompose.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/decompose.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Implements the **Decompose** phase — creates an epic via `br`, then iteratively prompts the agent to read a spec file and create beads from it until the agent signals the spec is fully decomposed.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `async function runDecompose(projectDir, flags)` — Entrypoint for the decompose phase; returns a `LoopResult`\n\n**Dependencies:** `./engine.js` (`runPhaseLoop`, `PhaseCallbacks`), `./template.js` (`loadTemplate`, `renderPrompt`), `./config.js` (`resolveModel`), `./beads.js` (`runBr`, `getAllBeads`), `./types.js` (`DecomposeFlags`, `LoopResult`); external: `fs`\n\n---\n\n## `src/reverse.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/reverse.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Implements the **Reverse** phase in two modes: **interactive** (SSE-driven with `clack` question prompting for the human user) and **autonomous** (engine loop that reads inputs and iteratively refines a Markdown spec document).\n\n**Exports:**\n- `async function runReverse(projectDir, flags)` — Entrypoint; dispatches to `runInteractive` or `runAutonomous` based on `flags.interactive`\n\n**Dependencies:** `./engine.js` (`runPhaseLoop`, `PhaseCallbacks`), `./template.js` (`loadTemplate`, `renderPrompt`), `./config.js` (`resolveModel`, `loadConfig`), `./opencode.js` (`startServer`, `connectToServer`), `./interactive.js` (`runInteractiveSession`, `createInteractiveClient`, `loadMockAnswers`, `clearMockAnswers`), `./skills.js` (`loadSkill`, `getCliDir`), `./types.js` (`ReverseFlags`, `LoopResult`), `./run-state.js` (`startRunTracker`), `./timeout.js` (`withTimeout`); external: `fs`, `path`\n\n---\n\n## `src/init.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/init.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** Scaffolds a new project with all required super-ralph artifacts: creates `.super-ralph/` directory, copies template files, generates `config.toml`, installs the OpenCode plugin, initializes the `.beads/` workspace via `br init`, and updates root `AGENTS.md`.\n\n**Exports:**\n- `async function runInit(projectDir)` — Idempotent initialization routine; skips files that already exist\n\n**Dependencies:** `./skills.js` (`getCliDir`); external: `fs`, `path`\n\n---\n\n## `src/index.ts`\n\n**Path:** `src/index.ts`\n\n**Purpose:** The CLI entrypoint (`#!/usr/bin/env bun`) — parses command-line arguments and dispatches to the appropriate phase runner (`forward`, `decompose`, `reverse`, `init`, `status`, `doctor`, `help`).\n\n**Exports:** Nothing (script entrypoint). Contains internal functions:\n- `parseArgs(args)` — Simple `--flag value` / boolean flag parser\n- `cmdForward(flags)`, `cmdDecompose(flags)`, `cmdReverse(positionals, flags)`, `cmdStatus(flags)`, `cmdDoctor(flags)` — Command handlers\n- `printUsage()` — Prints full help text\n\n**Dependencies:** `./forward.js` (`runForward`), `./decompose.js` (`runDecompose`), `./reverse.js` (`runReverse`), `./init.js` (`runInit`), `./beads.js` (`getEpicProgress`, `getAllBeads`), `./config.js` (`loadConfig`), `./opencode.js` (`checkBrokenSymlinks`), `./run-status.js` (`getRunStatus`), `./types.js` (`ForwardFlags`, `DecomposeFlags`, `ReverseFlags`, `LoopResult`); external: `fs`\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph Summary\n\n```\ntypes.ts          ← (no src/ deps — pure types)\noutput-parser.ts  ← (no src/ deps)\ntimeout.ts        ← (no src/ deps)\nskills.ts         ← (no src/ deps)\nrun-status.ts     ← (no src/ deps)\ntemplate.ts       ← (no src/ deps)\n\nbeads.ts          ← types\nconfig.ts         ← types\nprogress.ts       ← types\nevents.ts         ← types\n\nrun-state.ts      ← events\nopencode.ts       ← types, output-parser\ninteractive.ts    ← types, output-parser\n\nengine.ts         ← config, opencode, progress, types, events, run-state, timeout\n\nforward.ts        ← engine, beads, template, progress, config, types\ndecompose.ts      ← engine, template, config, beads, types\nreverse.ts        ← engine, template, config, opencode, interactive, skills, types, run-state, timeout\n\ninit.ts           ← skills\nindex.ts          ← forward, decompose, reverse, init, beads, config, opencode, run-status, types\n```\n</task_result>"
